SIMPLE: proverb
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proverb
<hw>Prov"erb</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>proverbe</ets>, F. <ets>proverbe</ets>, from L.
<ets>proverbium</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> before, for + <ets>verbum</ets> a
word. See <er>Verb</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An old and common
saying; a phrase which is often repeated; especially, a sentence which
briefly and forcibly expresses some practical truth, or the result of
experience and observation; a maxim; a saw; an adage.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer. Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A striking or paradoxical assertion; an obscure
saying; an enigma; a parable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His disciples said unto him, Lo, now speakest thou plainly, and
speakest no <qex>proverb</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>John xvi.
29.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A familiar illustration; a subject of contemptuous
reference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou shalt become an astonishment, a <qex>proverb</qex>, and a by
word, among all nations.</q> <rj><qau>Deut. xxviii. 37.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A drama exemplifying a proverb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Book of Proverbs</b></col>, <cd>a canonical book of the
Old Testament, containing a great variety of wise maxims.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Maxim; aphorism; apothegm; adage; saw.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proverb</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Proverb
<hw>Prov"erb</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To name in, or as,
a proverb.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Am I not sung and <qex>proverbed</qex> for a fool ?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To provide with a proverb.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am <qex>proverbed</qex> with a grandsire phrase.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proverb</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Proverb
<hw>Prov"erb</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To write or utter
proverbs.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proverbial</ent>⟦br⟧
